# Right-clicking on the editor body (not the gutter) opens a text-
# scoped context menu with LSP / fold / select-all-occurrences /
# Save items. SEV-2 VS-Code-mouse hunt finding (2026-06-07):
# "Editor text body has no right-click context menu — every other
# surface has one; text is the blind spot."
write doc.txt "ED01\nED02\nED03\nED04\nED05\nED06\nED07\nED08\nED09\nED10"
open doc.txt
command view.toggle_tree

# Right-click in the editor body — screen row 5 (editor starts at
# row 2), col 40 (well past any gutter).
rightclick 40 5
expect screen contains "Go to definition"
expect screen contains "Find references"
expect screen contains "Hover info"
expect screen contains "Rename symbol"
expect screen contains "Toggle fold"
